-- IRS Says It Wasn't Trying to Hide Targeting of Groups
-- B y   R i c h a r d   R u b i n
-- 2013-05-14T23:05:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-14/irs-says-it-wasn-t-trying-to-hide-targeting-of-groups.html
The U.S.  Internal Revenue Service 
said it didn’t disclose targeting of nonprofit groups based on
ideology because officials didn’t want to interfere with an
inspector general’s investigation.  “There was no intent to hide this issue,” the agency said
in a statement tonight.  To contact the reporter on this story:
